## Version Control

### Branching Strategy

- **`{{BASE_BRANCH}}`** â€” primary integration branch
- **Feature branches** â€” `TICKET-xxx` format, branched from `{{BASE_BRANCH}}`
- **Release branches** â€” cut from `{{BASE_BRANCH}}` when ready

### Pull Request Guidelines

- **Base branch**: `{{BASE_BRANCH}}`
- **PR title format**: `{Ticket-ID}: {Story Title}`
- **Assignee**: Always assign to yourself (`--assignee @me`)

### Git Rules

- Never force push to `{{BASE_BRANCH}}`
- Stage specific files â€” never `git add -A` or `git add .`
- No commits with failing tests
- Only maintainer can approve merges to `{{BASE_BRANCH}}`

## Security

### Data Protection
- **No real PII in git** â€” never commit database files, uploaded documents, or CSVs with real personal data. Use synthetic test data only.
- **No credentials on disk** â€” `.env` should have placeholders only. Real secrets belong in a vault or CI secrets. Rotate immediately if exposed. Never put secrets in client-exposed env vars (`NEXT_PUBLIC_*`, `VITE_*`, `REACT_APP_*`).
- **No PII in logs** â€” use opaque IDs, not names/emails/personal numbers. Configure structured logger redaction.
- **Flag third-party PII sharing** â€” any code sending personal data to external APIs (AI providers, analytics) must be reviewed for DPA compliance.

### Authentication & Authorization
- **Auth must fail closed** â€” if auth configuration is missing, DENY access. Never default to open. Add a production startup guard.
- **No insecure secret defaults** â€” session secrets must not have hardcoded fallback values. Crash if not configured.
- **CSRF protection** on all state-changing form endpoints (POST/PUT/DELETE). API-only apps with Bearer tokens are exempt.
- **Enforce roles in routes** â€” if roles exist in the data model, route handlers must check them. Roles in the DB but not in code = no access control.
- **Identity from session only** â€” never accept reviewer/approver/user identity from request body or query params.
- **Validate redirects** â€” redirect targets must be relative paths. Never redirect to user-supplied absolute URLs.
- **Session cookies**: `Secure=true`, `HttpOnly=true`, `SameSite=Strict` (or `Lax`) in production.

### General
- No secrets in code â€” use environment variables and `.env`
- Validate all input at system boundaries with a schema library (Zod, Pydantic, etc.)
- Review dependency updates for security advisories
- Keep `.env` and credential files in `.gitignore`
- Never set `ignoreBuildErrors: true` or equivalent â€” type errors can hide security bugs
- Rate limit authentication, AI, and file upload endpoints
- Never use `Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *` with credentials â€” use an explicit origin allow-list
- Validate outbound URLs from user input â€” block private IP ranges to prevent SSRF
- Sanitize uploaded filenames (strip path separators, reject `..`) to prevent path traversal

