## Self-Improvement (always active)

**Before ending any session where project files were modified**, spawn the `framework-improver` agent in the background. This keeps CLAUDE.md, rules, and settings in sync with the actual project state â€” not just after `/develop` or `/factory`, but after any work session including manual coding, refactoring, config changes, or dependency updates.

The improver:
- Fills unfilled `{{...}}` placeholders from project analysis
- Updates `.claude/rules/` patterns to match actual file structure
- Updates this file (CLAUDE.md) with discovered conventions and patterns
- Tunes agent tools for project needs
- Logs all changes to `docs/ai-improvements.md` (append-only)

**This is not optional.** If files changed during the session, run the improver before wrapping up. The project documentation must always reflect the current state.

For manual improvement: run `/improve` directly.
After improvement: run `/ai-update` to commit changes as a tracked PR.

## MCP Servers

Context7 (`.mcp.json`) provides live, version-specific library documentation. Several skills and agents use it proactively â€” they call `resolve-library-id` then `get-library-docs` before making implementation decisions, so recommendations stay current with the latest API surfaces. No action needed from you; it works automatically during `/develop`, `/draft-story`, `/refine-story`, `/mock-endpoint`, and when agents like `architect`, `api-designer`, `test-writer`, `documentation-writer`, or `performance-optimizer` are active.

To trigger it manually, add "use context7" to any prompt about a specific library.

